      • setStartTime

        public void setStartTime(int year,
                         int month,
                         int day,
                         int hour,
                         int minute)
        Set the object's startTime according the given parameters. The values are allowed to overflow (for example, sending a month value of 15) because the GregorianCalendar class allows it.
        Parameters:
        year - the year in which the event now starts
        month - the month in which the event now starts
        day - the day of the month in which the event now starts
        hour - the military time hour of the day in which the event now starts
        minute - the minute of the hour in which the event now starts

      • inConflict

        public boolean inConflict(Event otherEvent)
        Return a boolean value - true if the event and the otherEvent have conflicting times, false if they do not. If the events overlap at any point at all, they are in conflict. *If the events both start at the exact same time or end at the exact same time, then they are in conflict.
        Parameters:
        otherEvent - an Event object reference for comparison
        Returns:
        a boolean value representing the time conflict status between the two event objects

      • equals

        public boolean equals(Event otherEvent)
        A simple .equals method for comparing two event objects. If the objects share starting times and ending times, then they are heuristically considered equal.
        Parameters:
        otherEvent - an Event object reference for comparison
        Returns:
        a boolean value representing the equivalence of the data from two event object references
